Question: How can I submit my IT declaration?
Answer:
IT declaration can be submitted from April to December. The declaration window will be opened on the 21st of each month & closed on the 30/31st of the same month. 
The employees have 10 days’ time for updating the IT declaration. 

Once the employee logins to the portal. The employee needs to click on “SALARY” tab – then click on “IT DECLARATIONS”. If the declaration window is enabled its shows “OPEN”, then the employee needs to click on “START NOW”, enter all the declarations & submit. If the window is closed it shows “LOCKED”. 

If the declaration window is enabled an email intimation will be sent to the employee.

Question: There is a difference in my CTC and salary in hand, what is the breakup of my salary?
Answer: CTC means Cost to Company which covers all the benefits paid to employees by the company. It includes Gross salary, Employer PF and Gratuity. Gross salary includes all salary components like Basic, HRA, conveyance, medical, & special allowances. But it excludes Employer PF & Gratuity. Salary in Hand means the amount, which is received after deducting Employee PT, Group Medical Insurance, Professional Tax, TDS (Income tax) from gross salary. Salary in Hand will vary from employee to employee based on their Income tax and IT declarations made for the year

Question: What is the difference between the new and old tax regime?
Answer: Under the old tax regime, the employee can show all the deductions u/s 80C, 80D, 80G etc. Employees can claim allowances like HRA with higher income tax slab rate. But under the new tax regime the above deductions are not available, but the income tax slab rate is less.  The employee should compare their tax liability with both the regime. Based on the tax benefits the employee needs to select either the old or new tax regime. The tax slabs may vary as per notification by Government during yearly budget announcements

Question: How is the statutory deduction in my salary structured?
Answer:
There are four types of deductions – 
a.	Employee Provident Fund - will be a fixed deduction of Rs. 1,800.
b.	Professional Tax - will be a fixed deduction of Rs. 200
c.	Group Medical Insurance (GMI)
d.	Tax deducted at source (TDS or Income Tax)

GMI will be based on the CTC slabs below:
Level	Salary range (CTC/Month)	GMI deduction / month
L-1	23,118  - 26,000	150
L-2	26,001 - 37,000	250
L-3	37,001 - 50,000	300
L-4 	50,001 -  70,000	350
L- 5	70,000 - 100,000	400
L- 6	Above 100,000	450

TDS or Income tax deductions is completely based on the individuals tax planning. 
**ESI is deducted if applicable

Question: How is gratuity collected and paid?
Answer: Gratuity is collected from the CTC of every employee. It is applicable to the employees who have worked for a minimum term of 5 years. When the employee resigns after working for 5 years, then the employee is entitled to receive gratuity. If the employee resigns without completing 5 years, then no gratuity will be paid.

When the employee resigns after working for 5 years, then the employee is entitled to receive gratuity. If the employee resigns without completing 5 years, then no gratuity will be paid.

Question: How can I get set-up for with Provident Fund with my bank account?
Answer:
a.	Employees can login to their UAN portal www.unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in, under “manage” tab, select “KYC” option from drop down menu. 
b.	Select “Documents”, enter “bank account number and IFSC” and click save.After saving new bank details, it will show “KYC pending for approval”. 
c.	Submit “Documents” to Employer. 
d.	After documents verification by Employer, “KYC pending for approval” will change to “Digitally Approved KYC”. 
e.	Employees will receive a confirmation message from EPFO, after successful verification of bank details by employer.

Question: How can I ensure I am prepared for my annual performance review?
Answer:
Here are a few suggestions on how to approach your performance review - 
a.	Meet with your reporting manager well in advance (8-9 months) to understand your clear goals and KPIs, so that you have sufficient time to work on them.
b.	Set and review your targets every 3 months and schedule regular catchups to ensure you are headed in the right direction
c.	Layout your ambitions for the future and how you wish to contribute to your current or future positions
d.	Inform your manager of any additional contributions you have made to the organization beyond your daily scope of work
e.	Share any certifications completed by you for aiding you or uplifting your quality of work in your current / future positions  
f.	Keep track of your accomplishments throughout the year

e.	Share any certifications completed by you for aiding you or uplifting your quality of work in your current / future positions  
f.	Keep track of your accomplishments throughout the year

Question: What are the consequences of not completing my notice period?
Answer:
Shortfall of notice period shall be recovered from the employee at the rate of monthly total base compensation. This amount must be paid by the employee in the form of an Online Transfer in favor of “VALENTA BPO SOLUTION PVT LTD” on or before his/her last working day.   

a)	In case an employee fails to complete his/her clearances and fails to clear all outstanding dues before his/her last day with the company, his/her settlement will be foreclosed, and the company will issue demand letters for the recovery of outstanding dues. 
b)	No relieving / experience letters will be issued in such cases till such time the outstanding dues are cleared. 
c)	Further, the company reserves the right to initiate appropriate legal measures for recovery of such dues.
